1776609335151807	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtsAQ		item.create	bn-3w0	{"description":"# Context\n\nAfter a successful `kb compile`, `state/graph.json` does not exist. But `gather_status` and `run_inspect` both call `Graph::load_from(root)` and count nodes whose IDs start with `source-document-`, `wiki-page-`, `concept-` to populate the status counters.\n\nResult: `kb status` always shows \"wiki source pages: 0, wiki concept pages: 0\" even after compile produces 4 source pages and 45 concept pages. Same fallout for `kb inspect` — ID resolution through the graph fails.\n\n# Repro\n\n```\nkb init --root /tmp/kb3\nkb ingest <four-files>\nkb compile             # wiki/sources/ and wiki/concepts/ populated on disk\nls state/graph.json    # ENOENT\nkb status              # shows wiki pages: 0, wiki concept pages: 0 (wrong)\n```\n\n# Root cause\n\nCompile's per-pass work emits `BuildRecord`s with `input_ids` / `output_ids` / `output_paths`, but nothing assembles them into a persisted `Graph` or writes `state/graph.json`. The `Graph` struct in `kb_compile::lib` exists and has `save_to`/`load_from`, but `run_compile_with_llm` never populates or saves it.\n\n# Fix\n\nAfter all passes complete successfully in `run_compile_with_llm`, build a Graph from the manifest + build_records and call `graph.save_to(root)`. Nodes:\n- `source-document-<id>` for each normalized source (from `normalized/*/`)\n- `wiki-page-<slug>` for each wiki/sources/*.md (from source_summary build records' output_ids)\n- `concept-<slug>` for each wiki/concepts/*.md (from concept_merge build records' output_ids)\n\nEdges from build records' input_ids -> output_ids.\n\n# Acceptance\n\n- `state/graph.json` exists after a successful compile\n- `kb status` shows correct wiki-page and concept counts after compile\n- `kb inspect <wiki-page-slug>` resolves via graph lookup","kind":"bug","title":"compile never writes state/graph.json; status+inspect counts always zero"}	blake3:SnavrNI63pUyKiFVE431b6a8S-f1K6B9gCPZHlVgHvA
1776609335187671	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtsQQ		item.update	bn-3w0	{"field":"urgency","value":"urgent"}	blake3:x-ozxbKj_6sd3Mj0M53hW2bw1CQvlpgLp8jQ_axlOnY
1776609346807185	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtsgQ		item.create	bn-2bv	{"description":"# Context\n\n`kb lint --check stale` on a healthy KB produces false-positive errors:\n\n```\n[Error] wiki-source-src-04aca3d1:0 build record 'build:source-summary:src-04aca3d1' points to a missing output\n```\n\nEvery source_summary build record fails this check even though the page exists on disk.\n\n# Root cause\n\n`BuildRecord.output_ids` stores synthetic IDs like `wiki-source-src-04aca3d1` (matching the frontmatter id:). `BuildRecord.output_paths` stores the real path `wiki/sources/src-04aca3d1.md`.\n\nThe stale lint check (`detect_stale_artifacts`) treats `output_ids` values as filesystem paths and checks for their existence. That never succeeds since `wiki-source-src-04aca3d1` is not a path.\n\n# Fix\n\nIn `detect_stale_artifacts`, use `record.metadata.output_paths` to resolve existence, and use `output_ids` only for graph identity. Specifically: when flagging a missing-output, check `record.metadata.output_paths.iter().all(|p| !root.join(p).exists())` — if at least one output path exists, the record is fresh.\n\n# Acceptance\n\n- `kb lint --check stale` on a healthy post-compile KB reports zero issues\n- Intentionally deleting one wiki source page still triggers the stale finding\n- Existing lint tests updated to use output_paths","kind":"bug","title":"stale lint mistakes output_ids for file paths; false-positives on every source page"}	blake3:Jg459JVZhGsPqhVmERuLnezibTLnK6XS9BgdkzjpK80
1776609359947123	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtswQ		item.create	bn-2nx	{"description":"# Context\n\nConcept pages produced by `run_concept_merge_pass` have a YAML `sources:` block listing source anchors:\n\n```yaml\n---\nid: concept:global-interpreter-lock\nname: Global Interpreter Lock\naliases:\n- GIL\nsources:\n- heading_anchor: python-gil\n  quote: The Global Interpreter Lock (GIL) is a mutex...\n---\n```\n\nBut `kb lint --check missing-citations` expects the fields `source_document_id:` / `source_document_ids:` / `source_revision_id:` / `source_revision_ids:`. It does not recognize `sources:` as evidence of grounding, so it flags every concept page as \"synthetic region is missing source ids in frontmatter and citations\".\n\nOn a 4-source KB, all 45 concept pages trip this warning.\n\n# Fix options\n\n1. Extend `concept_merge::render_concept_page` to ALSO emit `source_document_ids: [...]` (and perhaps `source_revision_ids:`), resolved by walking `members[].source_anchors` back to their source documents.\n2. Extend `missing-citations` lint to recognize the `sources:` YAML block (with heading_anchor entries) as valid grounding.\n\nOption 1 is preferred — puts the true source IDs into the frontmatter where every other consumer expects them.\n\n# Acceptance\n\n- Concept pages have `source_document_ids:` in frontmatter listing the src-xxxx IDs of contributing sources\n- `kb lint --check missing-citations` reports zero issues on a freshly-compiled concept page\n- `source_document_ids` is derived from the members' `source_anchors` provenance","kind":"bug","title":"concept pages missing source_document_ids; missing-citations lint false-positives"}	blake3:sGPOKN73bagzDy-jW_QkddQUMXOXOunGREwIwNzsF5U
1776609375882331	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEttAQ		item.create	bn-azu	{"description":"# Context\n\nBacklinks on every concept page show \"_None yet._\" even when 3+ sources reference that concept via the YAML `sources:` block. Example: `wiki/concepts/global-interpreter-lock.md` has `sources:` pointing at `rev-73a14ce1#python-gil`, but its backlinks section is empty.\n\nRoot cause: the `backlinks` pass (`crates/kb-compile/src/backlinks.rs`) scans wiki pages for `[[wiki/concepts/...]]` markdown wiki-links and builds reverse references. But source pages emitted by `render_source_page` never contain such wiki-links — they cite using `rev-xxxx#anchor` text in a `## Citations` managed region, not `[[...]]` wiki-links.\n\nSo the backlinks pass never finds any references and every concept's Backlinks section stays empty.\n\n# Fix\n\nTeach the source-page renderer to emit wiki-links to concept pages it touches. The source_summary pass runs before concept_extraction + concept_merge, so at render time we don't yet know which concepts will be extracted. Options:\n\n1. Run a second source-page-enrichment pass AFTER concept_merge that walks concept pages' `sources:` blocks, groups by source_revision_id, and appends a managed `## Related concepts` region to each source page with `[[wiki/concepts/<slug>]]` links.\n2. In the backlinks pass, ALSO scan concept pages' `sources:` YAML frontmatter (not just markdown wiki-links) and credit each referenced source_revision_id with a backlink.\n\nOption 2 is simpler — backlinks pass already reads frontmatter for other passes. Make it also look at `sources[].heading_anchor` and the concept's own id.\n\n# Acceptance\n\n- After compile, every concept page with 1+ source anchor has a populated Backlinks section listing the referring source pages\n- Source pages gain a \"Referenced by\" managed region listing concept pages derived from their content\n- backlinks pass tests cover both wiki-link-based and frontmatter-source-based references","kind":"bug","title":"backlinks pass empty on concept pages (source refs use frontmatter sources:, not wiki-links)"}	blake3:5bidpOQbK7zExYjJ8Zeu8d81jM4KZky1Dyt2iOD_njM
1776609385180729	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEttQQ		item.create	bn-361	{"description":"# Context\n\n`kb ingest <non-existent-or-404-url>` prints:\n\n    error: fetch failed (non-retryable)\n\nNo URL, no status code, no hint about what happened. User has to guess.\n\n# Fix\n\nIn `crates/kb-ingest/src/url.rs::fetch_with_retry`, the Fatal variant's error already carries the `HTTP <status>` text from `do_fetch`. Improve the top-level wrapping via Context to include the URL being fetched:\n\n```rust\nErr(FetchError::Fatal(e)) => {\n    return Err(e).with_context(|| format!(\"fetch {url} failed (non-retryable)\"));\n}\n```\n\nAnd ensure `do_fetch` emits \"HTTP 404 Not Found\" style messages (include the canonical reason phrase from reqwest's status when available).\n\n# Acceptance\n\n- `kb ingest https://example.com/404` prints an error that names the URL and status code\n- `kb ingest https://bad.host` prints an error that names the URL and the DNS/connection failure\n- Non-retryable and retryable branches both include the URL","kind":"task","title":"ingest fetch errors do not include URL or status code"}	blake3:PNqeGLx1Cky-O3QPEqELO5vS_NxTdnoO-XXOQnJDzGM
