1776610805106431	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtzgQ		item.move	bn-361	{"state":"done"}	blake3:9LOc2CXxlCeA6DMbmZV67UWUR99QtWXf-M3jHfhfspc
1776613806734118	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtzwQ		item.create	bn-1g5	{"description":"# Context\n\nError output via `eprintln!(\"error: {err}\")` in main.rs:199 only prints the outermost anyhow context. When anyhow errors are chained (e.g. `source_error.context(\"fetch {url} failed (non-retryable)\")`), only the outer context reaches the user; the inner error (HTTP status, filesystem cause, etc.) is hidden.\n\nExample: after bn-361, `kb ingest https://.../404` prints:\n\n  error: fetch https://.../does-not-exist.md failed (non-retryable)\n\nbut should print:\n\n  error: fetch https://.../does-not-exist.md failed (non-retryable): HTTP 404 Not Found\n\n# Fix\n\nChange `eprintln!(\"error: {err}\")` to `eprintln!(\"error: {err:#}\")`. anyhow's `{:#}` formatter joins the full chain with `: ` separators. One-character change, affects every error path.\n\n# Acceptance\n\n- kb ingest against a 404 URL prints both the URL and the HTTP 404 in one line\n- Other commands' errors also show their full cause chain (compile failure with underlying IO error, ask with LLM error, etc.)\n- No behavior change when an error has only one context level","kind":"task","title":"error output hides inner anyhow causes (use {err:#} not {err})"}	blake3:brgDAAwpgY4Ulac0x3_U5vo5KRtUsi0S_9MIyJhU7Xc
1776613824392159	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEt0AQ		item.create	bn-358	{"description":"# Context\n\nA concept page with `source_document_ids: [src-xxxx]` AND `sources: [{quote: \"...\"}]` in its YAML frontmatter still trips the missing-citations lint:\n\n  [Warning] wiki/concepts/rust.md:15 synthetic region is missing citations in the page body\n\nThe check expects `[[wiki-link]]` or `[N]`-style markers inside the body of the synthetic region. But concept pages put their provenance in the frontmatter, not body text — that is the established format (render_concept_page writes `sources:` + `source_document_ids:` frontmatter and a short definition body).\n\n# Root cause\n\nIn `crates/kb-lint/src/lib.rs::detect_missing_citations`, the check flow is roughly:\n- has_sources = frontmatter contains source_document_ids or source_revision_ids\n- has_citations = page body has wiki-links / citation anchors\n- if has_sources && has_citations: pass; else emit warning\n\nFor concept pages, we have has_sources=true but has_citations=false, so the warning still fires.\n\n# Fix\n\nThe frontmatter `sources:` block (written by concept_merge with heading_anchor + quote entries) is structured, page-level citations. The lint should treat its presence — combined with `source_document_ids:` — as satisfying the grounding requirement for concept pages. Specifically:\n\n- If frontmatter has non-empty `sources:` list AND non-empty `source_document_ids:`, the page is adequately grounded regardless of body citations.\n- Keep the existing body-citations check for question-answer pages and source pages (where body citations are the norm).\n\nOr more conservative: only apply body-citation requirement to wiki/questions/*.md and wiki/sources/*.md.\n\n# Acceptance\n\n- Concept pages with source_document_ids + sources do not trigger missing-citations warnings\n- Concept pages WITHOUT either field still trigger (preserves the catch-a-bug property)\n- Promoted question pages still require body citations\n- Add a test for the concept-page path","kind":"bug","title":"missing-citations lint flags concept pages that do have frontmatter sources"}	blake3:wKVT2S__VQnOgOzThQFAefgzkMP0j5nVu_wZ4_tptPM
1776613838491440	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEt0QQ		item.create	bn-3p2	{"description":"# Context\n\nAfter bn-azu, backlinks correctly cross-link source pages and concept pages when the concept's `sources:` list has `heading_anchor` entries. But concept_merge can produce `sources:` entries with only a `quote:` field (no heading_anchor) — e.g. when the LLM didn't match a specific section:\n\n  sources:\n  - quote: \"This is the main source code repository for Rust.\"\n  - quote: \"It contains the compiler, standard library, and documentation.\"\n\nThe bn-azu implementation builds its reverse index via `heading_anchor -> source_document_id` lookup, so these no-anchor entries are silently skipped. Result: `wiki/concepts/rust.md` has `source_document_ids: [src-4846dd29]` in frontmatter but `Backlinks: _None yet._` because the backlinks pass couldn't find a heading_anchor match.\n\n# Fix\n\nWhen a concept page carries `source_document_ids` directly in its frontmatter, use those as an authoritative fallback: credit each source with a backlink from the concept. The `heading_anchor` path (which gives richer anchor-level links) remains primary; `source_document_ids` is the fallback for no-anchor entries.\n\nUpdate `crates/kb-compile/src/backlinks.rs` to scan each concept's `source_document_ids:` YAML field in addition to the existing `sources[].heading_anchor` path. Credit the source_document_id both ways (concept gets backlink, source gets \"Referenced by concepts\" entry).\n\n# Acceptance\n\n- Concept with `sources: [{quote: \"...\"}]` and `source_document_ids: [src-xxxx]` has non-empty Backlinks after compile\n- Source page's Referenced-by-concepts section lists the concept\n- Heading-anchor path still works (no regression)","kind":"bug","title":"backlinks pass skips concept sources: entries without heading_anchor"}	blake3:voN8bOXTq78mjZ2_nms0t9wfBWoh-DN-XKDPpJbAdUE
1776613851714653	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEt0gQ		item.create	bn-1a8	{"description":"# Context\n\n`kb lint` on a KB where every finding is severity=Warning returns:\n\n  error: lint succeeded with 2 warning(s)\n  exit code: 1\n\nTwo problems:\n\n1. **Word \"error:\" is misleading** when the report itself indicates success with warnings. Makes CI scripts / users think a hard error occurred.\n2. **Exit code 1 doesn't reflect the user's policy**. `[lint] missing_citations_level = \"warn\"` implies warnings should NOT fail the build. Currently any non-empty findings list (even all-warnings) produces exit 1.\n\n# Repro\n\n```\nkb init /tmp/kb-clean-with-warns\n# ... ingest, compile such that missing-citations warns on some pages\nkb lint\n# error: lint succeeded with 2 warning(s)\n# exit=1\n```\n\n# Fix\n\nIn `crates/kb-cli/src/main.rs::run_lint`:\n\n- Exit 0 when report has no findings OR only warnings\n- Exit 1 when any finding has severity=Error\n- Exit 2 only on hard crashes (IO, invalid config — existing behavior)\n\nAlso drop the \"error: lint succeeded...\" wording. When warnings exist:\n- stdout shows the warnings (as today)\n- no \"error:\" prefix on any final line\n- exit 0\n\nIf users want strict behavior (warn→fail), add a `kb lint --strict` flag.\n\n# Acceptance\n\n- `kb lint` with only warnings exits 0, no \"error:\" prefix in output\n- `kb lint` with any error finding exits 1\n- `kb lint --strict` (new flag) exits 1 on warnings\n- Update integration tests that assert exit codes","kind":"bug","title":"lint exits 1 with confusing \"error: lint succeeded\" when only warnings present"}	blake3:0ThU8IpgqJaZ1BwkB69IgTphNM4E9saS3HzklpCje3k
1776613858729494	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEt0wQ		item.update	bn-1g5	{"field":"labels","value":{"action":"add","label":"hands-on-sweep-4"}}	blake3:zGB0zuHISRD-4khxOrmETNchLvrMQ96jZhMhTpFiJqQ
