1776727341499799	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtrQY		item.create	bn-125l	{"description":"Repro: `kb serve` + GET /wiki/concepts/<any>. The YAML frontmatter (---\\nid:\\nname:\\n---) renders as a <p> of raw key:value text above the real content on every wiki page.\n\nRoot cause: in crates/kb-web/src/markdown.rs, the source is handed to pulldown-cmark without stripping the YAML frontmatter block. pulldown-cmark doesn't treat the leading --- as YAML, so it parses 'id: concept:aries\\nname: ARIES\\naliases:' as a paragraph and the list items as an unordered list.\n\nFix: in render_markdown (or the caller in server.rs), if the source starts with '---\\n', find the next '---' line, and slice from there. Keep it defensive (no frontmatter → no-op).\n\nAcceptance:\n- GET /wiki/concepts/aries returns HTML that does NOT contain 'id: concept:aries' in the body.\n- GET /wiki/sources/<src-id> same.\n- Page without frontmatter renders unchanged.\n- Integration test in crates/kb-web/tests/ seeds a fixture page and asserts frontmatter keys are not in the rendered HTML.\n- just check passes.","kind":"task","title":"fix(web): kb serve leaks YAML frontmatter into rendered page body"}	blake3:RmYiRGYBEW8TCold7vQaqXcPKxsEzu3dE5T3uY-QgUo
1776727352243178	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtrgY		item.create	bn-3tju	{"description":"Two bugs in the missing_concepts extractor (crates/kb-lint/src/lib.rs).\n\n## Bug 1: multi-word regex crosses paragraph boundaries\n\nPattern: \\\\b[A-Z][A-Za-z]+(?:\\\\s+[A-Z][A-Za-z]+){1,3}\\\\b\n\n\\\\s+ matches newlines, so 'FooBar System' at end of paragraph N and 'The FooBar' at start of paragraph N+1 merge into the candidate 'FooBar System The FooBar'. Same cause flags 'Tree Storage Engines The', 'Optimization The' when a sentence-starting stopword (The/This/…) begins the next paragraph.\n\nFix: scan paragraph-by-paragraph (split on blank lines) or use [ \\\\t]+ instead of \\\\s+ so the word-connector can't cross newlines. Paragraph-split is more robust — also peel 'The/This/…' at the END of the candidate by extending strip_leading_stopwords into a two-sided peel.\n\n## Bug 2: backtick-identifier regex admits plain English words\n\nPattern: `([A-Za-z][A-Za-z0-9_\\\\-./:]{2,63})`\n\nAdmits 'country', 'price', 'append', 'template' etc. — pure-alpha English words in inline backticks. For a KB, these are noise, not concepts.\n\nFix: require at least one cap letter, digit, or non-alpha char (., /, :, -, _). In other words, reject candidates that match ^[a-z]+$ — pure lowercase alpha-only words are not worth flagging.\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- Unit test: scanning 'FooBar System enables X\\\\n\\\\nThe FooBar System ...' produces candidate 'FooBar System' with 2 mentions, not 'FooBar System The FooBar'.\n- Unit test: backticked 'country' does NOT produce a candidate; backticked 'recLSN' / 'go/types' / 'FooBar' / 'LSM_tree' DO.\n- Re-run on /tmp/kb-pass14 corpus at min=1 confirms no cross-paragraph junk, no short-English-word backtick hits.\n- just check passes.\n\n## Don't\n\n- Don't change the stopword list.\n- Don't change the min_sources/min_mentions defaults.","kind":"task","title":"fix(lint): missing-concepts regex produces junk candidates (cross-paragraph spans + loose backtick shape)"}	blake3:r84oWSbFo74yjvYi63WxqMB8a9jJiR4hjPJApRMBzso
1776727364670415	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtrwY		item.create	bn-2rq6	{"description":"Two CLI-side cosmetic bugs.\n\n## Bug 1: concept-candidate review narrative is stale\n\n`kb review show lint:concept-candidate:<...>` prints:\n\n> On approve: the decision is recorded; creating the concept page from mentions via LLM is not yet implemented (see bone spec 'Approve workflow'). Work around by creating wiki/concepts/<slug>.md manually, then run 'kb compile'.\n\nAlso the review item's `Comment` field reads: \"… Approve to draft wiki/concepts/<slug>.md from the mentions (LLM step currently stubbed — see bone bn-31lt).\"\n\nBoth are from the pre-bn-lw06 world. bn-lw06 implemented the LLM-driven approve flow end-to-end. These strings actively mislead users into thinking the feature is missing.\n\nFix:\n- In kb-cli review.rs's print_pending_kind_narrative (or equivalent): replace the 'not yet implemented' text with the actual approve behavior: 'On approve: an LLM drafts wiki/concepts/<slug>.md from the source mentions and refreshes backlinks + indexes.'\n- In kb-lint/src/lib.rs where the review item's Comment is constructed: strip the parenthetical '(LLM step currently stubbed — see bone bn-31lt)' clause.\n\n## Bug 2: lint issues render ':0' line placeholder\n\nOutput shape: `[Warning] :0 concept candidate 'X' …`\n\nThe ':0' comes from a Display impl that prints 'file:line' but here both are empty/zero. Looks like a column number. Either skip the ':0' entirely when the issue has no file/line, or use a dash.\n\nFix: in the lint print path (crates/kb-cli/src/main.rs::print_lint_check_report or the LintIssue Display), conditionally omit the ':line' suffix when line is 0 (or missing).\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- `kb review show lint:concept-candidate:<id>` does NOT say 'not yet implemented' or 'stubbed' — it describes the real approve behavior.\n- The review-item JSON's Comment has no '(LLM step currently stubbed …)' fragment.\n- `kb lint` output has no stray ':0' prefix on warnings that lack a line number.\n- just check passes.\n\n## Don't\n\n- Don't alter actual approve behavior.\n- Don't renumber/remove the review items themselves.","kind":"task","title":"fix(cli): stale 'not yet implemented' narrative on concept-candidate review; drop :0 placeholder on lint output"}	blake3:rzf1gLCKO8SrhaAnjM5Ft4EefPaBvELOIFSeqG_rPaA
1776727375951063	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtsAY		item.create	bn-39fw	{"description":"bn-eqx7 added `category:` to concept pages (LLM assigns it during merge). bn-lw06's concept-candidate approve path writes new concept pages but the category field is often missing from the output even though the prompt (generate_concept_from_candidate.md) asks for it.\n\nRepro: `kb review approve lint:concept-candidate:foobar-system` → wiki/concepts/foobar-system.md is created. Frontmatter:\n\n    ---\n    id: concept:foobar-system\n    name: FooBar System\n    source_document_ids:\n      - src-20v\n      - src-4r3\n      - src-bcv\n    ---\n\nNo category, no aliases either.\n\nLikely cause: the LLM returned no category when the snippets are uninformative (honest), but the writer emits None → omits the field entirely. Fix options:\n1. Prompt: strengthen the instruction — category must be non-empty, pick a plausible fallback like 'uncategorized' or derive from the candidate's top parent source's category if the source has one.\n2. Writer: if the LLM returns no category, fall through to 'uncategorized' so wiki/concepts/index.md groups it under the existing 'Uncategorized' bucket (which bn-eqx7 already renders) rather than having a truly missing field.\n\nPick option 2 — it's closest to the bn-eqx7 convention and doesn't make the model guess.\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- After `kb review approve concept-candidate:<id>`, the generated concept page has a `category:` field (either LLM-assigned or literally 'uncategorized' as a fallback).\n- When the LLM assigns a category, it's preserved verbatim.\n- Integration test: stubbed LLM returning no category → written page has `category: uncategorized`.\n- wiki/concepts/index.md after approval includes the new concept under its category group (or under Uncategorized if fallback).\n- just check passes.\n\n## Don't\n\n- Don't remove the LLM-assigned category if it's present.\n- Don't change the bn-eqx7 index rendering logic.","kind":"task","title":"fix(lint): concept-candidate approve doesn't emit category: frontmatter (bn-eqx7 integration gap)"}	blake3:4Rord4qwkT4G-xtIOarwe1AAkZssAxNadxijdoxuN7M
1776727415685130	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtsQY		item.move	bn-125l	{"state":"doing"}	blake3:WcYxa_ovKdj2Ks0n0KINnpg2hdxg5LXAGj-RZF8a5_Q
