1776736918004661	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtygY		item.create	bn-1ikn	{"description":"bn-31uk added kb_query::strip_tool_narration with two anchors: first markdown heading, or last blank-line-separated paragraph. If the LLM produces narration and caption on consecutive lines with NO blank line between them AND no heading, the function returns the text unchanged — narration still leaks.\n\nThe worker flagged the pass-15 real-world sample (/tmp/kb-pass15/outputs/questions/q-db1/answer.md) hits exactly this shape:\n\n  Checking the output location, then I'll write and run a minimal matplotlib script to generate the PNG.\n  Writing the chart script now, then I'll execute it and verify the PNG was created.\n  The chart shows a simple horizontal comparison...\n\nNo blank line → strip_tool_narration returns everything.\n\n# Fix\n\nSwitch the chart call site to opencode --format=json and extract the phase: 'final_answer' event from the JSON event stream (opencode 1.4.3 supports this per worker's report). Apply only to --format=chart to avoid disturbing other adapter calls.\n\n# Acceptance\n\n- q-db1-style narration (no blank line) gets stripped — answer.md starts with the caption, no 'Checking/Writing' lines.\n- Heading-anchored caption still works.\n- Non-chart formats (md, json, marp) unchanged.\n- Integration test using the real pass-15 narration shape.\n- just check passes.\n\n# Don't\n\n- Don't change opencode output format globally; only the chart call path.\n- Don't remove strip_tool_narration — keep it as a fallback for runners that don't support --format=json.","kind":"task","title":"fix(ask): chart narration strip misses no-blank-line-separator case (follow-up to bn-31uk)"}	blake3:1TCjCnkxiVYcE5Z_P2m8ilogr6e1v916Jw7KPmko_OE
