1776782622907590	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEt0QY		item.create	bn-19r7	{"description":"bn-3nvm made the multimodal resolver actually pick up images (fixed bn-3dkw's dead-code bug), which exposed a latent argument-ordering bug in bn-3dkw's opencode invocation. When any image attachment is present, kb fails with:\n\n    LLM unavailable: opencode exited with error: File not found: # Question: ...\n\nRoot cause: crates/kb-llm/src/opencode.rs::build_command_with_attachments puts `-f <path>` BEFORE the prompt positional. opencode's yargs config marks --file / -f as [array], which in yargs means the flag greedily consumes subsequent positionals as additional file paths. So `opencode run -f image.png \"prompt text\"` parses to `-f [image.png, \"prompt text\"]` and opencode bails with 'File not found: prompt text'.\n\nRepro (direct):\n- opencode run -f /tmp/foo.png \"what is this\" → File not found: what is this\n- opencode run -f /tmp/foo.png -- \"what is this\" → works\n- opencode run \"what is this\" -f /tmp/foo.png → works\n\n# Fix\n\nIn crates/kb-llm/src/opencode.rs::build_command_with_attachments: emit the prompt positional BEFORE the -f flags, so yargs has already consumed the positional by the time -f starts slurping. Alternatively, insert a '--' separator between the last flag and the prompt.\n\nPick 'prompt before -f' — it's the simplest and doesn't depend on opencode honoring '--'.\n\n# Acceptance\n\n- `kb ask` on a corpus where the retrieval picks up images produces a real answer (not 'LLM unavailable: File not found').\n- Integration test in crates/kb-llm/src/opencode.rs: build_command_with_attachments with image_paths.len() > 0 emits prompt BEFORE any -f flag.\n- Existing tests (plain-text, no attachments) continue to pass.\n- End-to-end: /tmp/kb-pass15 'What colors appear in the diagram' produces a real LLM answer with the image attached.\n- just check passes.\n\n# Don't\n\n- Don't remove the -f flag plumbing.\n- Don't change other adapter calls.\n- Don't add a '--' separator as the primary fix (keep it simple — prompt-first works).","kind":"task","title":"fix(ask): opencode -f flag slurps prompt; put message before -f"}	blake3:KVSS8bVqctlpE8KrzEnzpexPwWDDRjoGZ4ZXWFfU8uY
