1776784619496707	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEt1QY		item.create	bn-2xbq	{"description":"The kb root currently mixes browseable dirs (wiki, outputs, reviews, raw, kb.toml) with internal plumbing (cache, logs, state, trash, normalized, prompts). Make the vault root cleaner by moving all internal dirs into a hidden .kb/ subdirectory (matches .git/ convention, Obsidian hides dotfiles by default).\n\n## New layout\n\n<root>/\n├── .kb/                ← all plumbing (HIDDEN)\n│   ├── cache/\n│   ├── logs/\n│   ├── state/\n│   ├── trash/\n│   ├── normalized/\n│   └── prompts/        ← user prompt overrides if they exist\n├── kb.toml\n├── raw/                ← original ingested inputs\n├── wiki/               ← compiled wiki\n├── outputs/            ← ask answers, slides, charts\n└── reviews/            ← review queue items\n\n## Implementation\n\n1. Centralize path constants in crates/kb-core (create a new module if one doesn't exist, e.g. `paths.rs`). Define:\n   - `KB_DIR = \".kb\"`\n   - helpers: `cache_dir(root)`, `logs_dir(root)`, `state_dir(root)`, `trash_dir(root)`, `normalized_dir(root)`, `prompts_dir(root)` — each returns `root.join(\".kb\").join(\"<name>\")`.\n2. Grep-and-replace every literal `\"cache\"` / `\"logs\"` / `\"state\"` / `\"trash\"` / `\"normalized\"` / `\"prompts\"` path construction across ALL crates (kb-core, kb-ingest, kb-compile, kb-llm, kb-lint, kb-cli, kb-query, kb-web). Route through the kb-core helpers.\n3. Update `kb init` to create the new layout (with `.kb/` pre-created).\n4. Update default kb.toml generation so `prompt_templates_dir` points at `.kb/prompts` (if that setting exists — check).\n5. Update `.kbignore` / .gitignore defaults so `.kb/` is excluded from ingest walks.\n6. Update any test fixtures / integration tests that hardcode the old paths. Prefer letting tests use the constants.\n\n## Migration command\n\nAdd `kb migrate` subcommand that, in the current root:\n- Detects legacy layout (any of cache/, logs/, state/, trash/, normalized/, prompts/ at root level).\n- `mkdir -p .kb`\n- `mv` each legacy dir into `.kb/`.\n- Leaves browseable dirs (wiki, outputs, reviews, raw) untouched.\n- Prints what it moved.\n- Idempotent — running on an already-migrated kb is a no-op.\n\nAlso: at the entry of `kb compile`, `kb ask`, `kb lint`, `kb status`, `kb review`, `kb serve`, detect legacy layout and print a helpful error pointing to `kb migrate`. Do NOT auto-migrate — make the user opt in via the explicit command.\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- `kb init` in a fresh dir creates `.kb/` + the usual browseable dirs. Root listing shows only browseable items.\n- `kb ingest` + `kb compile` write into `.kb/*` for internal state, `raw/` for inputs, `wiki/` + `outputs/` for artifacts.\n- `kb ask` still works; prompt overrides from `.kb/prompts/` take priority over bundled defaults.\n- Multimodal retrieval (bn-3nvm) still resolves `.kb/normalized/<id>/source.md` correctly.\n- `kb serve` endpoints unaffected (they read wiki/ + outputs/ which didn't move).\n- `kb migrate` on a legacy layout moves everything correctly; running again is a no-op.\n- Running `kb compile` on a legacy layout prints a clear error pointing at `kb migrate` (doesn't silently work on the old layout or corrupt state).\n- All integration tests pass against the new layout.\n- just check passes.\n\n## Don't\n\n- Don't carry backward-compat code that reads either location. Hard switch — `kb migrate` is the bridge.\n- Don't move wiki/, outputs/, reviews/, raw/, or kb.toml. Those stay at the root.\n- Don't auto-migrate on compile — it's a destructive-ish operation, keep it explicit.\n- Don't create a config setting to toggle the layout. One layout, period.\n- Don't change the on-disk format of files inside each dir — just move the dirs.","kind":"task","title":"refactor(layout): move internal dirs into .kb/ (cache, logs, state, trash, normalized, prompts)"}	blake3:iQPbwZsMn89RR_3j2vig1s98s3mBR0buAfXnQxhYL6Y
