1776818965723579	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEt4QY		item.create	bn-18qs	{"description":"bn-1geb's IMAGE_REF_RE pattern is `!\\\\[([^\\\\]]*)\\\\]\\\\(([^)\\\\s]+)\\\\)`, which excludes whitespace in the URL and doesn't handle CommonMark's angle-bracket-wrapped URL syntax (`![alt](<url with spaces>)`). Obsidian and screenshot tools emit both — e.g. `![](<./Screenshot from 2026-04-07 10-37-54.png>)`.\n\nRepro (pass-17 finding on ~/chief/consulting/kb):\n- normalized/src-1wz/source.md contains ![](<./Screenshot from ....png>) — no assets/ dir created, refs never rewritten.\n- Multimodal retrieval (bn-3nvm reuses the same regex shape) also misses them → kb ask sees zero image context.\n\n# Fix\n\nUpdate the regex in crates/kb-ingest/src/image_refs.rs and the mirror in crates/kb-query/src/images.rs to accept:\n1. Plain paths without whitespace: `![alt](path.png)` — today's behavior.\n2. Angle-bracket-wrapped URLs: `![alt](<url with spaces.png>)` — CommonMark extension.\n3. Optional title attribute: `![alt](path.png \"title\")` — discard the title (bn-1geb noted titles aren't supported; make them tolerated now).\n\nSuggested pattern (Rust regex flavor):\n  `!\\\\[([^\\\\]]*)\\\\]\\\\(\\\\s*(?:<([^>]+)>|([^)\\\\s\"]+))(?:\\\\s+\"[^\"]*\")?\\\\s*\\\\)`\n\nCapture group 2 (bracketed path) or capture group 3 (plain path) — callers take whichever matched.\n\nThen in scan_and_stage (and the multimodal resolver): when reading the path, trim any whitespace. File-exists check then uses the decoded path directly — no percent-decode v1.\n\n# Acceptance\n\n- Markdown body `![](<./Screenshot from 2026-04-07.png>)` produces a staged asset and rewritten `![](assets/Screenshot from 2026-04-07.png)` reference (or a safer basename — see basename collision handling below).\n- `![x](a.png \"title\")` stages a.png; title is discarded.\n- Existing tests (URL refs, data URIs, missing files) still pass.\n- Re-ingesting ~/chief/consulting/kb's src-1wz / src-1d5 sources now populates .kb/normalized/src-1wz/assets/ with the Screenshot PNGs, and the source.md has rewritten refs.\n- kb ask on multimodal-relevant question attaches the screenshots (verify via retrieval_plan or end-to-end).\n- just check passes.\n\n# Basename collisions\n\n`Screenshot from 2026-04-07 10-37-54.png` has spaces — the current normalized-write path uses Path::file_name() and renames on collision. Spaces should survive. If that breaks any downstream (wiki markdown escape etc.) percent-encode the basename; flag it in the report.\n\n# Don't\n\n- Don't percent-decode URL-style paths — we're handling filesystem references.\n- Don't remove the URL / data-URI skip paths.\n- Don't rename files gratuitously — preserve user basenames when unique.\n- Don't change the fallback behavior when a ref fails (still leave ref byte-identical in rewritten markdown).","kind":"task","title":"fix(ingest): image-ref regex misses angle-bracket-wrapped paths and paths with spaces"}	blake3:Jdbch7zOmcW5g7sWockQ7ipewgX2ptflAVBO4gpUs4k
