1776878292282970	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEt5QY		item.create	bn-nlw9	{"description":"Currently wiki/sources/src-1wz.md and outputs/questions/q-1xk/ are id-only; hard to tell what they are when browsing. Concepts already use slugs. Extend the pattern to sources and questions.\n\n# New names\n\n- `wiki/sources/src-1wz.md` → `wiki/sources/src-1wz-2026-04-07-liveramp-usb-team-intro.md`\n- `outputs/questions/q-1xk/` → `outputs/questions/q-1xk-produce-a-mermaid-graph-of-usb-team/`\n\nID is always first so prefix-match lookups (kb inspect, kb forget, kb review) still work. Slug follows after a `-` separator. Cap slug length at e.g. 60 chars; truncate on word boundary.\n\n# Keep id-only\n\n- `.kb/normalized/src-xxx/` — internal, not browsed. Don't touch.\n- `raw/inbox/src-xxx/` — internal. Don't touch.\n\n# Slug drift\n\nTitles can change (user edits source note title; user rephrases a question — rare). Two options:\n1. Freeze slug at first write, persist as part of metadata (e.g. `file_slug` in normalized metadata). Recompile preserves it. Stable but forever reflects the initial title.\n2. Re-slugify from current title on each compile; rename the file; update every backlink.\n\nPick option 2 — matches concept-page behavior (canonical-name changes rename the concept page today; backlinks machinery from bn-i5r / bn-2zy / bn-i5r refreshes the graph). Backlinks already refresh at end of compile, so this comes mostly for free as long as the write step moves the file rather than leaving the old one behind.\n\n# Implementation\n\n## Sources (wiki/sources)\n\nIn `crates/kb-compile/src/source_page.rs` (or wherever the source page writer lives):\n- Compute the slug from the source's title via the existing slugify util (whatever concept_merge uses). Cap at 60 chars, word-boundary truncate.\n- If title is empty or slug collapses to empty, fall back to just `<src-id>.md` (current behavior).\n- Write path is now `wiki/sources/<src-id>-<slug>.md`.\n- Before writing: if a stale file with the same `<src-id>-` prefix but different slug exists, delete it.\n- Update `wiki/sources/index.md` renderer in index_page.rs to produce the new filenames in the listing.\n- Update any other consumers that construct the source page path by `format!(\"wiki/sources/{id}.md\")` — grep kb-compile, kb-query, kb-lint, kb-cli for that pattern.\n\n## Questions (outputs/questions)\n\nIn `crates/kb-cli/src/main.rs::run_ask` (and/or the kb-query writer) where `outputs/questions/q-<id>/` is created:\n- Compute slug from the question text. Cap at 60 chars, word-boundary truncate.\n- Dir name becomes `q-<id>-<slug>`.\n- Relative refs inside the answer (`chart.png`, etc.) still work because they're relative to the dir.\n- `kb review`, `kb inspect`, promotion writer — find question dir by id prefix (glob for `q-<id>*`).\n\n## Migration\n\nAdd to existing `kb migrate` command (bn-2xbq): also walk `wiki/sources/` + `outputs/questions/` and rename any id-only entries to the slug-augmented form. Compute slug by:\n- For sources: read the wiki source page's frontmatter, extract `title`.\n- For questions: read `<q-id>/question.json` or `metadata.json`, extract the question text.\n\nAfter renaming, also run a backlink refresh so concept pages that linked to the old names get updated. Use the existing `refresh_backlinks` helper from bn-i5r.\n\nIdempotent: a second `kb migrate` is a no-op.\n\n# Identity invariants\n\n- Lookup by id still works: `kb inspect src-1wz` finds `wiki/sources/src-1wz-foo-bar.md` via glob `wiki/sources/src-1wz*` or `wiki/sources/src-1wz-*.md`. Add a `resolve_source_page_path(root, src_id)` helper in kb-core or kb-query.\n- Internal id parsing never sees the slug: always split on the first non-terseid char (`src-<terseid>` is 3-7 chars after `src-`, then any trailing `-<slug>` is cosmetic).\n- URLs / external links change. That's fine — this is a personal KB; no one has bookmarked them.\n\n# Acceptance\n\n- New kb: `kb ingest notes.md && kb compile` produces `wiki/sources/src-<id>-<title-slug>.md`.\n- New kb: `kb ask \"...\"` produces `outputs/questions/q-<id>-<question-slug>/answer.md`.\n- Title change: editing a source's title and re-ingesting causes the wiki source page to be renamed on next compile (old file removed, new file written, backlinks updated).\n- Empty title: falls back to `src-<id>.md` (no trailing dash).\n- Lookup by id: `kb inspect src-<id>` resolves to the renamed file. `kb forget src-<id>` moves the renamed file into trash.\n- `kb migrate` on a kb with legacy names renames them all, refreshes backlinks, second run is no-op.\n- Multimodal (bn-3nvm) and all other resolvers that map `wiki/sources/src-X.md → .kb/normalized/X/` keep working (they strip the slug when deriving the id).\n- Integration tests for each path.\n- just check passes.\n\n# Don't\n\n- Don't change `.kb/normalized/src-xxx/` or `raw/inbox/src-xxx/` layouts.\n- Don't change the on-disk contents of the source/question files — only rename.\n- Don't break existing id-based lookups (kb inspect, kb forget, kb review).\n- Don't carry backward-compat code that reads both name forms — the migrate bridges.\n- Don't use special characters in slugs — only `[a-z0-9-]+`, lowercase.\n- Don't silently truncate mid-word — cap on whitespace boundary before applying char limit.","kind":"task","title":"feat(layout): include slugified title in wiki/sources/* filenames and outputs/questions/* dir names"}	blake3:OVm8v2CcmFYd_zz1yAHtwMu8w37oD3gZjXOj96BAtGE
1776878339857989	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEt5gY		item.move	bn-nlw9	{"state":"doing"}	blake3:un5IQFbyFmX-FM5izBTrNNXrEO2um39KQjK-Yjng5Lk
