1776880029217862	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEt6gY		item.create	bn-6puc	{"description":"Two bugs exposed after bn-nlw9 migrate ran on ~/chief/consulting/kb:\n\n1. **Title extraction falls through to src-id when no H1/frontmatter title is present.** Results in wiki source page frontmatter `title: src-1wz`. Then bn-nlw9's slug writer dutifully produces `wiki/sources/src-1wz-src-1wz.md`. Five sources in the consulting kb hit this (src-290, src-1wz, src-ht9, src-1xo, src-1f1) — all markdown notes whose body starts with H2/H3 rather than H1.\n\n2. **Slug writer doesn't guard against a slug that equals/contains the src id.** Even with fix (1), if a user manually titles a note `src-1wz` (or something else that slugifies to the id), the writer would still produce the ugly double. \n\n# Fix\n\n## Root cause — title extraction fallback order\n\nIn the ingest path where the wiki source page's `title` gets set (grep kb-ingest / kb-compile for where the normalized metadata stores title). Extend the fallback order:\n\n1. Explicit `title:` frontmatter in the ingested markdown.\n2. First H1 (`# ...`) line in the body.\n3. **NEW:** filename stem with hyphens converted to spaces. E.g. `2026-04-07-LiveRamp-USB-team-intro.md` → `2026-04-07-LiveRamp-USB-team-intro`. Keep underscores/hyphens/case verbatim — the slug pass will lowercase and normalize.\n4. src id (last resort).\n\nStep 3 gives noticeably better titles on notes that organize by filename (typical Obsidian vault convention).\n\n## Safety guard — slug writer\n\nIn `kb_compile::source_page::source_page_path_for` (bn-nlw9's helper): after computing the slug, if the slug equals `src-<id>` or starts with `src-<id>-` (i.e. the user's title is itself id-like), skip the slug suffix and emit `<src-id>.md`. Same for the question dir writer.\n\n## Migrate also re-slugs stale renames\n\nExisting consulting kb already has `src-1wz-src-1wz.md` filenames. A `kb migrate` re-run should detect these (filename where the slug portion matches or contains the id) and rename to the clean form `src-1wz.md`. Keep idempotent.\n\nAdditionally, migrate should trigger a recompile-equivalent of source_summary for sources whose title is still just the src id — so that fix (1)'s new fallback updates the wiki source page's title field AND the filename. OR: print a note telling the user to re-ingest those sources if they want better titles.\n\nDecide: (a) migrate auto-re-summarizes (expensive LLM calls) or (b) migrate just updates the title field in-place from the new filename-stem fallback. Pick (b) — update the wiki source page frontmatter + managed-region title block directly from the filename (looked up via normalized metadata's ingest source path).\n\n# Acceptance\n\n- Ingest a markdown file with no H1 and no frontmatter title → wiki source page's `title` frontmatter equals the file's stem (e.g. `2026-04-07-LiveRamp-USB-team-intro`), not the src id.\n- Source page filename after compile is `wiki/sources/src-<id>-2026-04-07-liveramp-usb-team-intro.md` (slugified stem).\n- Explicit titles still win (don't regress).\n- H1 detection still wins over filename (don't regress).\n- Slug writer: if title slugifies to the src id or begins with it, the output filename is just `wiki/sources/src-<id>.md` (no ugly double).\n- Migrate on the consulting kb transforms existing `src-1wz-src-1wz.md` → a cleaner name; running again is a no-op.\n- just check passes.\n\n# Don't\n\n- Don't run expensive LLM re-summarization during migrate.\n- Don't break any test that asserts on explicit-title sources.\n- Don't change the on-disk format of the wiki source page beyond the `title:` frontmatter + the managed title block.\n- Don't change behavior when a proper title already exists.","kind":"task","title":"fix(ingest+compile): title fallback to filename; slug writer guards against src-X-src-X"}	blake3:KUFUwNKCmEp-w-wwmothre-hqrDfSRyE9oDX-K9xYis
1776880070700791	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEt6wY		item.move	bn-6puc	{"state":"doing"}	blake3:0Gk0HZrF2VB9JC9dCMpY_eFhCPqf9AJ8qm0NuV29Rjs
