1777073708039593	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEt8gY		item.create	bn-3qsj	{"description":"Add semantic retrieval as a second tier alongside the existing BM25-style lexical retrieval, fused via RRF. Pattern adapted from ~/src/bones (bones-search + bones-sqlite-vec).\n\n**See notes/semantic-retrieval.md for the full design** — schemas, threshold constants, fallback behavior, wiring, tests, and rationale (including why frankensearch was evaluated and rejected).\n\n# Scope\n\nPhase 1 + 2 from the design doc. Specifically:\n\n- New crate `kb-sqlite-vec` — sqlite-vec auto-extension shim (FFI)\n- New module `kb-query/src/semantic/{model.rs, embed.rs, search.rs}` — hash-embed backend (always available, zero new deps), incremental embedding pipeline, KNN with sqlite-vec fast path + Rust-side cosine fallback\n- New module `kb-query/src/hybrid.rs` — RRF fusion of lexical + semantic ranked lists\n- Storage: `.kb/state/embeddings.db` with `item_embeddings` + `semantic_meta` tables\n- Wire into `kb ask`, `kb search`, `kb serve /search`, `kb compile` (sync pass), `kb status` (summary line)\n- Config: `[retrieval] semantic = true / rrf_k = 60 / min_semantic_score = 0.15` plus `KB_SEMANTIC=0` env override\n- Threshold guards: MIN_SEMANTIC_SCORE = 0.15 and MIN_SEMANTIC_TOP_SCORE_NO_LEXICAL = 0.20\n\nOut of scope (deferred to Phase 2 follow-up bones):\n\n- ONNX / model2vec backends (feature-flagged, separate bone)\n- Cross-encoder rerank\n- ANN\n- Embedding normalized source bodies (only wiki pages in v1)\n- Structural graph signal\n\n# Acceptance\n\nPer the design doc 'Acceptance criteria' section. In short:\n\n- `kb compile` populates the embedding store; idempotent\n- `kb ask` retrieval uses hybrid; lexical-only behavior preserved when semantic is disabled\n- `KB_SEMANTIC=0` and `KB_SQLITE_VEC_AUTO=0` both produce identical top-k via the Rust cosine fallback\n- A fixture test where the relevant page uses different vocabulary from the query proves the semantic tier is doing real work\n- Threshold guards prevent garbage on out-of-corpus queries\n- `just check` passes\n\n# Don't\n\n- Don't add ONNX/model2vec in this bone — Phase 2.\n- Don't change `LexicalIndex` or its scoring — hybrid sits on top.\n- Don't change `RetrievalPlan` shape externally — additive fields only (`semantic_score`, `semantic_rank`).\n- Don't carry backward-compat code that reads pre-embedding-store kbs as 'broken' — first compile builds it from scratch silently.\n- Don't take an async runtime change (rusqlite is sync; wrap in spawn_blocking where needed).\n\n# References\n\n- notes/semantic-retrieval.md — full design\n- ~/src/bones/ws/default/crates/bones-sqlite-vec/ — FFI shim pattern\n- ~/src/bones/ws/default/crates/bones-search/src/{semantic,fusion}/ — embed + KNN + fusion patterns\n\nThe worker should read the design doc before writing any code.","kind":"task","title":"feat(retrieval): hybrid lexical+semantic search via kb-sqlite-vec + RRF fusion"}	blake3:Y8gUHwxQT0YjmcC0KO6Gejm5bvoEF-yXJBUvEG3yTM4
1777073891819749	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEt8wY		item.move	bn-3qsj	{"state":"doing"}	blake3:OYAbSwjgG2MUjzc7uFmiafvppJaZbxBJ1ja19ec5To4
