1777328976968963	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtnQc		item.comment	bn-2lp2	{"body":"=== Current state of work (session ending 2026-04-27 22:30) ===\n\n**Branch state.** Workspace ws/bn-2lp2 has 3 commits, scaffold + model\ndownload + hash refactor. Not yet merged. State: doing, owner kb-dev.\n\n**What's done:**\n\n1. New crate `crates/kb-ingest-audio/` registered in workspace Cargo.toml.\n2. `decode.rs`: pure-Rust container demux via symphonia → mono 16 kHz f32\n   PCM. Supports mp3/m4a/mp4/wav/flac. Linear resampler (good enough for\n   ASR; whisper does its own log-mel). 2 unit tests.\n3. `models.rs`: ModelStore with auto-download + hash verify. Cache root\n   defaults to ~/.kb/models, override via KB_MODELS_DIR env var.\n   ModelSpec.hash uses `<algo>$<lowercase-hex>` format, supports\n   `blake3` and `unverified` (sha256 stub returns Unsupported).\n4. All 3 model URLs verified working (200/302, no auth):\n   - SEGMENTATION_3_0: huggingface.co/onnx-community/pyannote-segmentation-3.0/resolve/main/onnx/model.onnx (5.7 MB, MIT)\n   - WESPEAKER_RESNET34_LM: github.com/k2-fsa/sherpa-onnx/releases/download/speaker-recongition-models/wespeaker_en_voxceleb_resnet34_LM.onnx (26 MB, Apache-2)\n   - WHISPER_LARGE_V3: huggingface.co/ggerganov/whisper.cpp/resolve/main/ggml-large-v3-q5_0.bin (1.1 GB, MIT)\n5. Real blake3 hashes captured + pinned in const literals:\n   - segmentation: 354861b95ce3746d10224527a92239eef345b6facc3f4cbbfc94ba52fb93993f\n   - wespeaker:    0efe839fb7f400913d0be2869158687c402921ed8cac492f18d60f0d1bbd9b65\n   - whisper:      2324b561c8e0fcf4cd2c0fde6b19a24a11ac27a4b629fe6687c794a309587840\n6. `examples/capture_model_hashes.rs` doubles as the recapture path if\n   upstream reissues anything (loud HashMismatch surfaces drift).\n7. `pipeline.rs`: TranscribeConfig, end-to-end transcribe() entrypoint,\n   speaker-assignment + same-speaker turn merge using the kbtx spec's\n   INTRA_TURN_GAP_SECONDS=10.0 / MAX_TURN_DURATION_SECONDS=300.0\n   constants. ASR + diarization calls are STUBBED with TODO(task #N).\n8. 12 unit tests pass.\n\n**Build pin to remember:** `ort = \"=2.0.0-rc.10\"` because rc.12 has a\nSend-trait regression (OperatorDomain not Send) that breaks pyannote-rs's\nSessionBuilder. Track upstream and unpin once fixed. The pin is in\ncrates/kb-ingest-audio/Cargo.toml directly, not workspace deps.\n\n**Stubbed / not yet wired (the next ~3 chunks of work):**\n\n- `pipeline::run_asr()` — needs whisper-rs FullParams setup, segment\n  iteration (start_t/end_t/text). whisper-rs 0.13 is in the lockfile.\n  Reference for params: faster-whisper used batch_size=16, language\n  auto-detect, no_speech_threshold filter. Output to AsrSegment {\n  start_seconds, end_seconds, text }.\n- `pipeline::run_diarization()` — needs pyannote-rs sliding-window\n  segmentation (10s windows, 2s hop), embedding extraction with knf-rs\n  fbank features, then clustering (cosine similarity). The crate\n  exposes EmbeddingExtractor + EmbeddingManager + Segment types but\n  docs.rs coverage is 0% — examples/ in the crate repo are the\n  reference. Output to DiarizationSegment { start_seconds,\n  end_seconds, speaker } where speaker is \"SPEAKER_NN\".\n- Once both work, kbtx render goes through kb_core::transcript (already\n  merged to default in bn-3h4h). The pipeline already calls render() on\n  a TranscriptDoc it builds correctly.\n\n**Acceptance criteria already met (from the bone description):**\n- Models live in ~/.kb/models/, auto-download on first use ✓\n- Single binary across CPU + (CUDA on Linux | Metal on macOS) — in\n  progress; whisper-rs feature flags will gate per-platform GPU\n- Output kbtx-equivalent to bn-3hfw — by-construction (same renderer)\n\n**Reference fixtures:** the two LiveRamp transcripts are already in\ncrates/kb-core/tests/fixtures/ as round-trip targets:\n- usb-team-intro.kbtx.md (188 turns, 6 speakers, 3 pauses)\n- delta-team-intro.kbtx.md (106 turns, 6 speakers, 8 pauses)\n\nThe cached artifact JSON for both meetings lives at\n~/.kb/cache/transcripts/<sha>.json — useful for A/B'ing the Rust output\nagainst the prototype's segments before going through the full ASR run.\n\n**Open task list (in TaskCreate state, will reset on session start):**\n- 153: ASR pipeline (whisper-rs)        [pending]\n- 154: Diarization pipeline (pyannote-rs) [pending]\n- 155: Merge ASR+diar → render kbtx     [pending — pipeline scaffolding done, just needs real inputs]\n- 156: CLI: kb ingest --audio <path>    [pending]\n- 157: Validate against USB + Delta vs prototype [pending]\n\nTasks 150 (scaffold), 151 (download/verify), 152 (decode) are complete.\n\n**Cross-references in repo:**\n- notes/transcript-spec.md (kbtx format spec) — merged to default in bn-3h4h\n- crates/kb-core/src/transcript.rs (parser/renderer) — merged to default\n- crates/kb-web/src/markdown.rs (anchor injection for `## @<id>` headings) — merged to default\n- tools/audio-transcribe/ (Python prototype) — merged to default in bn-3hfw"}	blake3:H9aLFpvdIQl6FjM61KfbCEkk3_Ujxqp6Vu76VXJo01A
1777329005668519	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtngc		item.comment	bn-2qda	{"body":"=== Evaluation update (2026-04-26 / 2026-04-27) ===\n\nEmpirical eval ran on six representative kb-corpus images (the originals\nthat motivated the screenshot-search use case): hex-arch text card,\nhorizontal bar chart, ML pipeline DAG, Excalidraw architecture diagram,\ncode editor screenshot, Garden build dashboard.\n\n**Verdict on the local-backend pick from the original bone description\n(\"Florence-2-large\"): replace it.**\n\nModels tested on RTX 3090:\n\n- SmolVLM-256M: heavy hallucinations + looping, **unusable**.\n- SmolVLM-500M: better but still loops on text-rich images, hallucinates\n  service names, **not viable** — captions would mislead retrieval.\n- **Qwen3.5-0.8B**: reads small text, identifies real Garden service\n  names, captures structural relationships in diagrams. Concise prose.\n  ~5–11 s/image GPU bf16. **Recommended local primary.**\n- Qwen3.5-2B: comparable to 0.8B; sometimes more concise, sometimes\n  loses tag-text detail the 0.8B preserves. Not worth the 2.5×\n  parameter budget for this corpus.\n\n**Dual-backend recommendation (revised from original):**\n\n```toml\n[compile.captions]\nenabled = true\nrunner = \"harness\"          # default: vision-capable LLM via opencode/claude\nmodel = \"claude-haiku-4-5\"\nallow_paths = [\"wiki/\", \"sources/\"]\n\n[compile.captions.local]    # opt-in\nbackend = \"qwen35-0.8b\"\ndevice = \"auto\"             # cuda → bf16; cpu → fp32 (NEVER bf16 on AVX2-only CPUs)\nfallback_to_harness = true\nmax_seconds_per_image = 90\n```\n\n**CPU traps to bake into impl** (validated on Ryzen 9 3900X, AVX2 only):\n\n- bf16 on a CPU lacking AVX-512_BF16 falls back to software emulation\n  → ~10× slower than fp32 (290s vs 28s for image 01). **Auto-detect\n  AVX-512_BF16 and only use bf16 on CPU if present.**\n- torch's int8 dynamic quant: same speed as fp32 + visibly degraded\n  caption quality without VNNI. **Never use for this on AVX2 CPUs.**\n- llama.cpp Q4_K_M GGUF + mmproj-F16: didn't finish in 12+ min/image\n  on this CPU. **GGUF path is not yet recommended** until validated on\n  AVX-512 hardware or with a different mmproj precision. Stick with\n  transformers fp32 as the CPU default for v1.\n\n**Detailed eval notes**, including per-image side-by-side outputs and\nall tooling references, were drafted at\n`ws/bn-2qda/notes/image-captioning-eval.md` (139 lines, committed in\nthat workspace but not yet merged to default — workspace went stale\nafter epoch advance). Recover the doc with `maw ws recover bn-2qda` if\nnot destroyed.\n\n**Vision LLM via the harness** (the default path) requires the runner\ncontract to grow an `image_paths` field. opencode + Claude Code both\nsupport vision input; the integration is conceptually small.\n\n**Cross-corpus cost note.** Per-image hash cache means each unique\nimage is captioned once, ever. ~$0.001–$0.01 per image at frontier\nprices, with cache → effectively a one-time cost."}	blake3:W92dmHIQIr-mL-gSbcGrmkGpCqZayRjYkl9fsGqGOq0
1777329030985376	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtnwc		item.comment	bn-3syy	{"body":"=== Pointers for picking this up ===\n\nThe kbtx parser/renderer landed in bn-3h4h (merged to default). Relevant\nfiles:\n\n- crates/kb-core/src/transcript.rs — has TranscriptDoc/RosterEntry/Turn\n  AST and a tested parser. Use `transcript::parse(&source)` then walk\n  `doc.body` to detect transcript shape (presence of any `BodyNode::Turn`).\n- crates/kb-core/tests/fixtures/{usb,delta}-team-intro.kbtx.md — real\n  transcripts you can use as test cases for the lint/extractor change.\n\nLikely fix sites in kb-compile:\n\n- The key_topics extractor that walks H2 headings. Look for whatever\n  emits `key_topics` frontmatter blocks (heading slugs become topics).\n  Check by `kb compile` output mentioning `key_topics` and seeing 188\n  entries on src-2zg or src-3gs.\n\nDetection strategy options (pick simplest that works):\n\n1. File extension: `.kbtx.md` files skip H2 → topic extraction entirely.\n   Cleanest signal.\n2. Frontmatter probe: `type: source` + body parses as transcript via\n   `kb_core::transcript::parse(...).body.iter().any(|b| matches!(b, BodyNode::Turn(_)))`.\n   More robust but slower.\n\nEither works; I'd start with extension + add frontmatter as a second\ngate if needed."}	blake3:E6iZx5sZeOnQ2drJrYP8FwOrvNPvhqXXjbMris6dKjM
1777329031017096	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtoAc		item.comment	bn-3hfw	{"body":"=== Done — locations after merge ===\n\nMerged to default in commit feat: WhisperX audio diarization prototype (bn-3hfw).\n\n- Tool: tools/audio-transcribe/ in default (uv-managed venv).\n- Cached artifact JSON: ~/.kb/cache/transcripts/<sha256-of-audio>.json\n  (re-runs with new render config are free — no ASR/diarization re-run).\n- Tested on two LiveRamp recordings:\n  - USB Team Intro (75 min, 6 speakers) → src-2zg in consulting kb\n  - Delta Team Intro (60 min, 6 speakers) → src-3gs in consulting kb\n- Format-spec lock-in landed in bn-3h4h (kbtx parser + renderer in\n  kb_core::transcript). Tool now emits .kbtx.md."}	blake3:wd10Ke1X9wtXF4url_ZUerpfVRuV4W4zReqLNtkkWTo
1777329031046775	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtoQc		item.comment	bn-3h4h	{"body":"=== Done — locations after merge ===\n\nMerged to default. Key artifacts:\n\n- notes/transcript-spec.md — kbtx format spec v0.1\n- crates/kb-core/src/transcript.rs — parser + renderer + turn_anchor()\n- crates/kb-core/tests/fixtures/{usb,delta}-team-intro.kbtx.md —\n  real-corpus regression fixtures\n- crates/kb-web/src/markdown.rs — H2 turn-heading anchor injection\n  (`## @<id> [HH:MM:SS → HH:MM:SS]` → `id=\"<id>-HH-MM-SS\"`)\n- tools/audio-transcribe/src/kb_audio_transcribe/kbtx.py — Python\n  renderer (Rust port of this is the same module's logic)\n\nAnchor format: `<id>-<HH>-<MM>-<SS>` so citations like\n`[src-foo#xiaodong-00-01-35]` resolve cleanly in kb-web.\n\nFollow-up bone bn-3syy tracks the kb-compile key_topics noise that\nsurfaces when transcripts have N speaker turns each emitting an H2."}	blake3:cNefHityB5jeJGxmF4vNH5Z9YUfENSnpNItnKhXSmcE
1777331253310094	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtogc		item.comment	bn-2lp2	{"body":"=== Session continuation 2026-04-27 evening ===\n\n**Completed since prior comment:**\n\n1. `pipeline::run_asr()` wired to whisper-rs 0.13:\n   - Loads whisper-large-v3-q5_0 from cached ModelHandles.whisper\n   - Greedy sampling (best_of=1), suppress_blank=true, no_speech_thold=0.6\n   - detect_language=true (matches WhisperX prototype default)\n   - whisper.cpp returns timestamps in 10ms units → divided by 100 for seconds\n   - All print_* flags off; tracing::info logs entry/exit only\n\n2. `pipeline::run_diarization()` wired to pyannote-rs 0.3:\n   - f32 mono PCM → i16 conversion via clamp + scale\n   - EmbeddingExtractor.new + EmbeddingManager(usize::MAX)\n   - get_segments() iterator → embedding_extractor.compute → search_speaker\n   - SEARCH_THRESHOLD = 0.5 (matches pyannote-rs example)\n   - Speaker IDs format SPEAKER_NN to match prototype\n\n3. `TranscriptArtifact` struct exposed publicly:\n   - Holds {duration_seconds, sample_rate, asr_model, diarization_model,\n     audio_filename, asr_segments, diarization_segments}\n   - Serialize/Deserialize for cache round-trips\n   - Pipeline split: produce_artifact() runs GPU work, render_artifact()\n     is pure → cheap re-render. transcribe() is the convenience wrapper.\n\n4. CLI: `kb ingest --audio <path>` with companions:\n   - --audio-title <STR> (default: filename stem)\n   - --audio-recording-date <YYYY-MM-DD> (default: today, derived w/o chrono)\n   - --audio-out <PATH> (default: <stem>.kbtx.md adjacent to audio)\n   - When --audio is set, sources can be empty\n   - Helper transcribe_audio_to_kbtx() lives next to run_ingest in main.rs\n   - Validates: audio file exists, no-source-no-audio fails fast\n\n5. `just check` is GREEN across the full workspace:\n   - Fixed pre-existing clippy nursery/pedantic issues in kb-core/transcript.rs\n     (unwrap→expect, missing-errors-doc, must-use, derive Eq, single-variant\n     match, items-after-statements, format-push-string)\n   - Suppressed unavoidable cast lints at crate level for kb-ingest-audio\n     (cast_lossless, cast_possible_truncation, cast_possible_wrap,\n      cast_precision_loss, cast_sign_loss, similar_names, doc_markdown)\n   - Fixed pre-existing kb-web/markdown.rs identical-arms + redundant guard\n   - Fixed pre-existing kb-core/tests/transcript_fixtures.rs unwrap_used\n\n**Tests:** 1140+ pass workspace-wide. kb-ingest-audio: 14 unit tests.\nAdded: render_artifact_round_trip_through_kbtx_parser,\nartifact_serde_round_trip, days_to_ymd_known_dates.\n\n**NOT done — task 157 (validate against USB + Delta):**\n\nSkipped because it requires:\n- ~1.2 GB model download on first call (~/.kb/models/ is empty)\n- ~30-60 min on CPU for the 75-minute USB recording, similar for Delta\n- Output then compared to crates/kb-core/tests/fixtures/{usb,delta}-team-intro.kbtx.md\n\nAudio files exist at:\n  /home/bob/chief/consulting/ops/chief/projects/liveramp/USB Team Intro/GMT20260407-143343_Recording.m4a\n  /home/bob/chief/consulting/ops/chief/projects/liveramp/Delta Team Intro/GMT20260409-143115_Recording.m4a\n\nValidation command (ready to fire):\n  TMPKB=$(mktemp -d) && /home/bob/src/kb/ws/bn-2lp2/target/debug/kb init \"$TMPKB\"\n  /home/bob/src/kb/ws/bn-2lp2/target/debug/kb --root \"$TMPKB\" ingest \\\n    --audio \"/home/bob/chief/consulting/ops/chief/projects/liveramp/USB Team Intro/GMT20260407-143343_Recording.m4a\" \\\n    --audio-title \"USB Team Intro\" \\\n    --audio-recording-date \"2026-04-07\" \\\n    --audio-out /tmp/usb-rust.kbtx.md\n\nExpected drift from prototype (per stack lock-in comment): few-% WDER vs\ncommunity-1, no word-level alignment (whisper.cpp doesn't do it), so\noutput schema differs from the cached prototype JSON (no `words` array).\n\n**Branch state.** ws/bn-2lp2 has 11 modified files, all changes uncommitted.\nTwo commits already on the branch: 9d8cf40 (scaffold) + cbce72f (download).\nRecommend committing this session's work as one feat commit before\nattempting the validation run, so a slow-running pipeline test doesn't\nrisk losing progress."}	blake3:tEtfo4zzPQUHtdLrF1on206onrMVTdxE8hgXvLR2JQE
1777341837305008	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtowc		item.create	bn-1xyb	{"description":"**Why.** pyannote-rs 0.3.4 has a bug that makes its segmentation\nunreliable on audio longer than ~30 seconds:\n\n- USB (75 min recording): segments=0 returned. Per-window argmax never\n  transitions speech→silence, so the iterator's emit logic never fires.\n- Delta (60 min) and a 5-min mid-meeting slice: emits a segment with an\n  empty samples slice (start_idx == end_idx), which crashes\n  knf-rs::compute_fbank with \"frames array is empty\".\n- Both behaviors reproduce with `ort` set to the CPU EP, ruling out the\n  ort/CUDA-EP issue documented in bn-2lp2.\n\nbn-2lp2 currently masks the failure with a try/catch fallback that\nlabels every ASR segment \"speaker_unknown_NNNN\" — output is a valid\nkbtx with whisper transcripts, but no speaker info.\n\n**Suspected root cause.** pyannote-rs/src/segment.rs accumulates an\n`offset` variable across all 10 s windows (frame_size=270 sample\nstride). After many windows, the offset drifts away from sample\nalignment, and segment-slicing math (`start_idx..end_idx` against\n`samples`) produces zero-length slices. The model's argmax behavior on\nlong inputs may also drift toward saturation.\n\n**Options.**\n\n1. **Fork/vendor pyannote-rs and patch segment.rs.** Smallest delta —\n   keep the rest of the API (EmbeddingExtractor, EmbeddingManager).\n   Track the fork in our tree as a path dep.\n\n2. **Reimplement segmentation in kb-ingest-audio.** Run the\n   pyannote-segmentation-3.0 ONNX model directly via `ort` with our\n   own per-window iteration + argmax + transition detection. Reuse\n   pyannote-rs's EmbeddingExtractor and EmbeddingManager (those work).\n\n3. **Switch to sherpa-onnx Rust bindings** (the fallback in the\n   bn-2lp2 plan). sherpa-onnx bundles a complete VAD + segmentation +\n   embedding pipeline and is widely used. Heavier dependency surface\n   than pyannote-rs but much more battle-tested.\n\n**Recommendation.** Option 2 — reimplement just the segmentation loop.\nLowest dependency footprint, leverages what already works (embedding\nextraction). The segmentation logic is ~50 LoC.\n\n**Acceptance.**\n- Fresh `kb ingest --audio` on USB and Delta produces kbtx files with\n  proper speaker labels (≥6 distinct speakers each, matching the\n  prototype's count).\n- Speaker labels are stable enough that turn-merging produces a turn\n  count within 2x of the prototype's 188/106.\n- No regression in CPU-only build.\n- `just check` stays green.\n\n**Reference fixtures.** USB and Delta kbtx fixtures in\ncrates/kb-core/tests/fixtures/ (from the WhisperX prototype) are the\ngold standard for comparison.\n\n**Cross-references.**\n- bn-2lp2 (closed once this lands) — the parent native-audio bone.\n- Audio files at /home/bob/chief/consulting/ops/chief/projects/liveramp/{USB,Delta} Team Intro/*.m4a\n- Models at ~/.kb/models/{segmentation-3.0.onnx, wespeaker-voxceleb-resnet34-LM.onnx}","kind":"task","labels":["audio"],"title":"ingest-audio: replace pyannote-rs (long-audio bug)"}	blake3:yDfcrasdCpPa5ZiCYxTNTvxJ42IA9XyU9WML9Cauvyc
1777341867463158	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtpAc		item.comment	bn-2lp2	{"body":"=== Validation run results (2026-04-27 evening, continued) ===\n\nWired up CUDA, hit two bugs along the way, validated end-to-end on the\nreal LiveRamp recordings.\n\n**Working / validated:**\n\n- `cargo build -p kb-cli --features cuda` produces a CUDA-linked\n  binary (~403 MB, vs ~293 MB CPU-only). Build env vars needed because\n  CUDA 13.1 dropped sm_52 and libcu++ requires C++17:\n\n      CUDA_PATH=/opt/cuda PATH=/opt/cuda/bin:$PATH \\\n      CMAKE_CUDA_ARCHITECTURES=86 CMAKE_CUDA_STANDARD=17 \\\n      CMAKE_CXX_STANDARD=17 \\\n      cargo build -p kb-cli --features cuda\n\n- whisper-large-v3-q5_0 on a 3090 runs ~10x realtime:\n  - USB 75-min recording → 2990 ASR segments in 7:30 wall\n  - Delta 60-min recording → 3550 ASR segments in 5:00 wall\n  - Spot-check of transcript text matches WhisperX prototype quality\n\n- Default CPU build still works (verified via `just check`).\n\n- Fault-tolerant pipeline: when diarization fails (see below), we log\n  a warning and produce kbtx with `speaker_unknown_NNNN` placeholder\n  IDs per ASR segment. The kbtx is valid and ingests through `kb\n  ingest --audio` cleanly.\n\n**Bugs found:**\n\n1. `set_detect_language(true)` made whisper return 0 segments. That\n   flag tells whisper.cpp to ONLY detect language, skipping the\n   transcription pass. Switched to `set_language(None)` for proper\n   auto-detect during full transcription. (Committed in 011117d.)\n\n2. `onnx-community/pyannote-segmentation-3.0` exports its output\n   tensor as `logits`, but pyannote-rs hardcodes a lookup for\n   `output`. Switched SEGMENTATION_3_0 to thewh1teagle/pyannote-rs\n   release mirror (the pyannote-rs author's MIT-licensed export with\n   the right tensor name). New blake3 hash captured. (Also in 011117d.)\n\n3. **ort 2.0-rc.10 CUDA EP produces wrong segmentation logits on long\n   audio.** With ort CUDA EP registered, pyannote's per-window argmax\n   saturates on one class, never transitions, no segments emitted.\n   Fix: don't enable ort/cuda. Whisper still gets GPU; pyannote stays\n   on CPU (model is 5.7 MB, finishes in ~1 second anyway). Committed\n   in 1935347.\n\n4. **pyannote-rs 0.3.4 has a long-audio segmentation bug,\n   independent of CUDA.** Repros on CPU-only too:\n   - 30 s clip works (14 segments).\n   - 5 min slice + 60 min Delta + 75 min USB all fail with either\n     \"segments=0\" or \"embedding failed: frames array is empty\".\n   - Filed as bn-1xyb. Suspected: offset/sample drift in\n     segment.rs's window iterator producing empty slice indices, plus\n     model output saturation on long sequences.\n\n   Worked around in 1935347 by catching the error and falling back to\n   per-segment placeholder speakers. Speaker labels in current rust-\n   produced kbtx are NOT meaningful — bn-1xyb tracks the proper fix.\n\n**Files validated:**\n- /tmp/usb-rust.kbtx.md — 14966 lines, 2990 turns, src-1cz on\n  ingest into a fresh test KB.\n- /tmp/delta-rust.kbtx.md — 17766 lines, 3550 turns, src-ygz on\n  ingest into a fresh test KB.\n\n**Branch state.** ws/bn-2lp2 has 5 commits ahead of default. Ready to\nmerge IF we accept that diarization is deferred to bn-1xyb. Otherwise,\nkeep this bone open and complete bn-1xyb first to land both together.\nSuggest the former — whisper transcription on its own is high-value,\nand the kbtx format already tolerates uniform-speaker fallback.\n\n**Time/perf reference for validation rerun after bn-1xyb lands:**\n8-9 min wall-clock per ~75-min recording on the 3090; 1.6 GB RSS\npeak; ~1.1 GB GPU memory."}	blake3:mVJ_WHkv7kvKZqP5XKgR-nm8lH67_QwYuGeLGpzh4aE
