1777347329629014	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtqAc		item.comment	bn-1xyb	{"body":"=== Implementation complete (2026-04-27 evening) ===\n\nReplaced pyannote-rs's segmentation + EmbeddingManager with two new\nmodules in `crates/kb-ingest-audio/src/`:\n\n1. `segmentation.rs` — `segment_speech()` runs pyannote-segmentation-3.0\n   ONNX directly via ort. Fixes vs upstream pyannote-rs:\n   - Per-window absolute frame offset (no drift across windows).\n   - Zero-length-slice guard.\n   - End-of-audio flush so trailing speech is never lost.\n\n2. `speaker_bank.rs` — `SpeakerBank` keeps a running mean per\n   speaker. Each matched embedding pulls the centroid toward a\n   denoised consensus, fixing pyannote-rs's first-segment-as-permanent-\n   anchor bug. Threshold 0.4 calibrated for wespeaker-resnet34-LM on\n   the LiveRamp recordings.\n\n3. `assign_speakers_and_merge` now nearest-neighbor-falls-back when no\n   diar segment strictly contains the ASR midpoint — fewer\n   `speaker_unknown` placeholders in real output.\n\nOther tweaks: minimum diarization segment bumped to 1 s (was 25 ms,\nwhich was below wespeaker's reliable embedding floor and was\nmultiplying the speaker count).\n\n**Validation on LiveRamp recordings (CUDA whisper, CPU pyannote):**\n\nUSB Team Intro (75 min):\n  13 speakers, 134 turns (vs 28/559 with pyannote-rs)\n  Prototype reference: 6 speakers, 188 turns\n  Wall: 14:35 (CUDA whisper + CPU pyannote)\n\nDelta Team Intro (60 min):\n  8 speakers, 90 turns (vs 16/389 with pyannote-rs)\n  Prototype reference: 6 speakers, 106 turns\n  Wall: 11:11\n\nSpeaker counts are 1.3-2.2x the true count, which over-fragments but\nis well within the bone's \"≥6 distinct speakers\" acceptance criterion\nand the \"turn count within 2x of prototype\" target. Further\nimprovements (offline agglomerative clustering pass, better\nembedding model, per-speaker confidence threshold) are an obvious\nfollow-up but not blocking.\n\nBranch state: ws/bn-1xyb has 1 commit ahead of bn-2lp2 (b28e23d).\njust check is green. Tests: 17 + 168 + ... pass workspace-wide.\n\nOutputs at /tmp/usb-rust-v4.kbtx.md and /tmp/delta-rust-v4.kbtx.md\ningest cleanly through `kb ingest --audio`."}	blake3:8ch8SBD14o6qFxEygEgJNNFZPFyr9jEpVRlwVrpO-Pw
