1777479215235258	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtvAc		item.create	bn-1319	{"description":"Currently `kb ask` writes plain `[N]` markers in answer bodies, which Obsidian renders as inert text. Rewrite valid citations in `postprocess_answer` (crates/kb-query/src/artifact.rs) to Obsidian wikilinks of the form `[[<wiki-path-without-md>(#anchor)?|N]]` using the citation manifest. Leave invalid `[N]` untouched so the unresolved-citations footer still works. Update tests, including a regression for the wikilink shape and one for invalid citations passing through. CITATION_RE is used only at the top of postprocess_answer (before the rewrite), so downstream parsers are unaffected.","kind":"task","title":"Make answer.md citations clickable in Obsidian"}	blake3:Lw1i8Y0jae4ZSBaT6gWTP6SN5UzG4SmE6YDOpYhIFlU
1777479219695492	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtvQc		item.create	bn-15w4	{"description":"Today the answer body starts with the model's prose; the original `raw_query` only appears in question.json. When opening the answer in Obsidian/Excalidraw the user has to round-trip to question.json to see what was asked. Render the question into the answer file — easiest is a header block above the body in `render_answer_frontmatter` (crates/kb-query/src/writer.rs) so frontmatter still parses cleanly, e.g. an H1 like `# Q: <raw_query>` followed by the body. Mirror it in render_answer_json's body or as a top-level field. Add tests asserting the question appears in answer.md.","kind":"task","title":"Include original question text in generated answer.md"}	blake3:bE1ZsD0PZgNjM7ERLmtE_Rt5CnRzDrRaXnzG37uLGjM
1777479228685196	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtvgc		item.create	bn-28ob	{"description":"Today `kb ask` only ships `md`, `json`, `marp`, `png`, and `chart` formats. The chart format already drives the model through opencode's bash/write tools to drop a PNG at a known path (see ask_chart.md prompt + chart plumbing in crates/kb-cli/src/main.rs around line 2060). Extend that pattern: add a `--format=excalidraw` (or sibling format) where we hand the LLM a sandbox dir under outputs/questions/<q-id>/ and a prompt instructing it to write one or more `.excalidraw` JSON files there using the Excalidraw schema. Move/keep the produced files in the q-dir alongside answer.md. The answer body should then reference each diagram with an Obsidian-friendly embed (`![[diagram.excalidraw]]`) so it renders in-place if the Excalidraw plugin is installed. Surface failures the same way chart does (write_chart_failure_artifacts pattern). Add a prompt template (excalidraw schema cheat-sheet for the model), wire format dispatch, and add a smoke test using a stub adapter.","kind":"task","title":"Allow ask to produce Excalidraw diagrams alongside answer.md"}	blake3:nUfe-N-Bg6LL572qk0HLGDYQaz8onm987TgI1G0gBSk
