1777479825029226	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtxAc		item.create	bn-3049	{"description":"After commit eb88a14 (`feat(llm): pass opencode/claude prompts via stdin, drop sh -c`), four kb-cli integration tests fail on default:\\n- ask_format_chart_produces_png_and_answer_with_image_ref\\n- ask_format_chart_strips_llm_tool_narration_preamble\\n- ask_format_figure_is_alias_for_chart\\n- review_approve_applies_concept_candidate_with_stub_llm\\n\\nThe chart fakes (install_fake_chart_harness, install_fake_narration_chart_harness, and the concept-merge stub) still parse the prompt out of argv, but kb-cli now feeds it via stdin. Update the shell stubs to read the prompt from stdin (e.g. `prompt=\\$(cat)` then grep) and confirm the test suite is green again.","kind":"task","title":"Fix integration test fakes after stdin-prompt change"}	blake3:tQEM-kwQxxPK_FCaogO06GPJx9sV4QKOZvb7R2bgdfI
