1777482434623361	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtyQc		item.create	bn-2cs2	{"description":"Today `kb ask` requires `--format=excalidraw` (etc.) to opt into diagram production. Make the default an `auto` mode where the model chooses what supporting artifacts to produce (none, an Excalidraw diagram, a matplotlib chart, or several) based on the question.\\n\\nDesign:\\n- New default format: 'auto'. Explicit `--format=md|marp|json|chart|excalidraw` still works as overrides for users who want to pin a specific output.\\n- Single unified prompt 'ask_auto.md' that always asks for a markdown memo + describes the optional sidecar artifact kinds (Excalidraw schema cheat-sheet, matplotlib chart-script instructions) and selection criteria.\\n- Always tool-enabled (write+bash) and structured_output=true on the auto path so opencode tool narration doesn't leak.\\n- Sandbox: `<q-dir>/.scratch/`. After the run, classify produced files by extension and promote to q-dir: `*.excalidraw[.md]` (diagrams), `*.png` (charts). Reject everything else. Sandbox is removed on both success and failure.\\n- Body: LLM's stripped reply, with a safety net that appends `![[name.excalidraw]]` / `![chart](name.png)` for any promoted file the model forgot to embed.\\n- Citations and question-block (bn-1319, bn-15w4) keep working unchanged.\\n- Trade-off accepted: every default ask is now tool-enabled (longer latency, more tokens). Users who need the cheap path use `--format=md` explicitly.\\n- ArtifactKind: AnswerNote (the markdown is the primary deliverable; figures are sidecars).\\n\\nNon-goals for v1:\\n- Auto-selecting marp / json output (those change the whole document type and need explicit `--format=`).","kind":"task","title":"Make ask --format=auto the default; let model multiplex outputs"}	blake3:bHmOzwdugbuMfu4__K90GzF7yjzoQZbfn9CZMxRVbGQ
