1777484503623507	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEtzQc		item.create	bn-1l1t	{"description":"`wiki/sources/<src>-<slug>.md` pages have a 'Citations' managed region that today renders entries as plain text (e.g. `- rev-3jevbz#unhygienix`). Obsidian shows them as inert text — no navigation.\\n\\nThe entries point at heading anchors in the normalized source content (`.kb/normalized/<doc_id>/source.md`). The wiki source page already references that location via `rewrite_summary_image_refs` (`../../.kb/normalized/<src>/...`), so the path convention is established.\\n\\nFix: in crates/kb-compile/src/pipeline.rs (the `citations_display` map around line 1190) format each citation as a markdown link of the form `[<anchor>](../../.kb/normalized/<doc_id>/source.md#<anchor>)` so it's clickable. Fall back to the source_revision_id as label/no-fragment when no heading anchor is set. Add tests for both cases.\\n\\nApplies to source pages produced by future `kb compile` runs; existing pages are stale and rebuild on the next compile when the source changes.","kind":"task","title":"Make wiki-source-page citations clickable in Obsidian"}	blake3:VYKfhS-IeSnGO0E-zIA4uMW9PV4lssooTbZLrgg-Y2c
