1777506835765327	kb-dev	itc:v3:AWLJ58k-Zk8zEAAAAAAAQde-r7a9sAAAAAEt3Qc		item.create	bn-3e4t	{"description":"Filed maw#bn-2oii reporting that `maw ws sync <ws> --rebase` produces a committed corrupt state when two workspaces append disjoint additive changes to the same file, even though plain `git rebase` handles it cleanly.\n\nEncountered while merging kb's bn-166d (citation verification) after bn-2hyr (OCR fallback) had already advanced the epoch — both bones independently extended `crates/kb-cli/src/{config,main}.rs` in different regions. Workaround used: `maw exec <ws> -- git reset --keep <pre-rebase-sha> && git rebase <epoch>`, then `maw ws sync` to clear stale metadata.\n\nCheck back during triage. To check for response from maw-dev:\n  rite history maw --from maw-dev --since 2026-04-29 --format json\n\nClose this tracking bone when bn-2oii is resolved, deferred, or otherwise responded to.","kind":"task","labels":["tracking"],"title":"[tracking] maw bn-2oii: ws sync --rebase corrupts additive-only edit overlaps"}	blake3:ViVgMixPJqOE9g5Ff-g5J6aPGPYde7YR0Wr0_UPwbpg
